About this hotel

In a commercial area amid businesses, this casual hotel is 19 minutes' walk from the Marrakech train station, and 3 km from both the bustling Jemaa el-Fnaa square and the 12th-century Koutoubia Mosque.

Check-in time: 2:00 PM
Check-out time: 12:00 PM

    Last time i stayed in this Gueliz hotel was 2018, and this time i choose it again - i think its a good answer how the hotel is.
    Very conveniently located in modern part of the city, ATM around the corner, grocery shops and cafes and restaurants around, 20min walk to the train station. I stayed all together 5 nights. Room facing the street are a bit noisy – be aware of this. During the Covid time it’s even more convenient as the testing Covid lab is opposite the hotel, across the street, with English testing certificate valid before flight. Definitely will be back there again!

    Gueliz

    The wide, French-era streets of Gueliz are home to upscale Moroccan and European restaurants, cabarets and chic bars, as well as art galleries and mainstream fashion stores. Created by the eponymous painter, and later owned by Yves Saint Laurent, the Majorelle Garden has grasses, cactuses, flowers and various elements painted cobalt blue. Near El-Harti Park, the Church of the Holy Martyrs has Moorish-style arches.

    About this hotel

    In a commercial area amid businesses, this casual hotel is 19 minutes' walk from the Marrakech train station, and 3 km from both the bustling Jemaa el-Fnaa square and the 12th-century Koutoubia Mosque. …

    Warmly decorated rooms come with free Wi-Fi and flat-screen TVs, as well as minifridges, safes and en suite bathrooms.

    An available breakfast buffet is served in a bright restaurant with floor-to-ceiling windows. Other amenities include an indoor pool with a terrace and loungers, as well as a guest lounge.
